title: The Frames, NPR All Songs Considered 26-04-07
description:
This is a copy of the Frames All Songs Considered Concert from April 26th 2007 in Washington D.C, recorded by npr.

I have put the whole thing through some very heavy compression and divided it up into  26 individual tracks.

This is designed to make it possible to listen to it in a noisy environment, such as on the bus or the street with a personal audio player. 

There was huge range in the levels on this recording, and the snare must have been getting into everything, it is so loud, he even burst it during the set! You can really here the compressor sucking it down. This is not for dynamic range audiophiles. If you don't know what I'm talking about, then it's likely that this version will sound 'better' to you.

Also, the original was 128kbps and I have encoded here at 192kbps CBR. 160 would have sufficed. I wasn't thinking of distribution at the time, and I don't feel like doing it again.

Thanks once again to the Frames for the music!!, and to npr for recording the show.


The Orginal Audio can be downloaded here: <a href="
http://www.npr.org/templates/story/story.php?storyId=9796328" rel="nofollow" target="_NEW">
http://www.npr.org/templates/story/story.php?storyId=9796328</a>
